{"title_page": "Andrian Candu", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Andrian Candu\n| image = A Candu 2.jpg\n| image_size = \n| office = Member of the [[Moldovan Parliament]]\n| office2 = 11th [[President of the Moldovan Parliament]]\n| president2 = [[Nicolae Timofti]]<br/>[[Igor Dodon]]\n| office1 = \n| predecessor2 = [[Igor Corman]]\n| successor2 = [[Zinaida Grecean\u00eei]]\n| office3 = [[Cabinet of Moldova|Deputy Prime Minister]]\n| birth_name = Andrian Candu\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1975|11|27|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Chi\u0219in\u0103u]], [[Moldovan SSR]], USSR\n| spouse = {{Marriage|Zuzana Stastna|2009}}\n| children = Daniel<br>Vera<br>Adam\n| party = Pro Moldova\n| alma_mater = [[Babe\u0219-Bolyai University]]\n| awards = [[File:Ordinul de Onoare.jpg|35px|link=Order of Honour (Moldova)]]\n| website = {{URL|www.candu.md}}\n| primeminister2 = [[Iurie Leanc\u0103]]<br/>[[Chiril Gaburici]]<br/>[[Valeriu Strele\u021b]]<br/>[[Pavel Filip]]\n| primeminister3 = [[Iurie Leanc\u0103]]\n| president3 = [[Nicolae Timofti]]\n| successor3 = [[Stephane Christophe Bride]]\n| termend2 = 24 February 2019\n| termend5 = 11 July 2014\n| termstart5 = 30 May 2013\n| predecessor5 = [[Vladimir Plahotniuc]]\n| successor5 = [[Sergiu S\u00eerbu]]\n| primeminister5 = [[Iurie Leanc\u0103]]\n| president5 = [[Nicolae Timofti]]\n| office5 = [[Moldovan Parliament|Deputy Speaker of the Moldovan Parliament]]\n| termend4 = 23 January 2015\n| termstart4 = 11 July 2014\n| predecessor4 = [[Valeriu Laz\u0103r]]\n| office4 = [[Ministry of Economy and Infrastructure (Moldova)|Minister of Economy]]\n| termstart2 = 23 January 2015\n| predecessor3 = [[Valeriu Laz\u0103r]]\n| successor4 = [[Stephane Christophe Bride]]\n| president4 = [[Nicolae Timofti]]\n| primeminister4 = [[Iurie Leanc\u0103]]\n| termstart = 30 November 2014\n| termend3 = 23 January 2015\n| termstart3 = 11 July 2014\n| termstart1 = 28 November 2010\n| termend1 = 11 July 2014\n| predecessor5 = [[Vladimir Plahotniuc]]\n}}\n'''Andrian Candu''' (born 27 November 1975, in [[Chi\u0219in\u0103u]]) is a [[Moldova]]n politician and a member of the Moldovan Parliament since December 2014. Since 23 January 2015 he has served as the [[President of the Moldovan Parliament|President]] of the [[Parliament of the Republic of Moldova]],<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pre\u0219edintele_Parlamentului_Republicii_Moldova|title=Presidents of the Parliament of the Republic of Moldova|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}{{Circular reference|date=April 2018}}</ref> though his claim to the office has been disputed by [[Zinaida Grecean\u00eei]] since 8 June 2019, as was part of the [[2019 Moldovan constitutional crisis|constitutional crisis]]. Before that, Candu was a [[Deputy Prime Minister]], [[Minister of Economy]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministerul_Economiei_(Republica_Moldova)|title=Ministry of Economy of the Republic of Moldova|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}{{Circular reference|date=April 2018}}</ref> of the [[Republic of Moldova]] since 3 July 2014, and served as [[Deputy Speaker]] of the Parliament of the [[Republic of Moldova]]. He was member of the Parliament of Republic of Moldova between December 2010, and July 2014.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://candu.md/despre-mine/|title=CV Andrian Candu|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170325024711/http://candu.md/despre-mine/|archive-date=25 March 2017|url-status = dead|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nAndrian Candu was born in November 27, 1975. After Andrian Candu finished his secondary education at school No. 25, currently Lyceum \"Onisifor Ghibu\", [[Chi\u0219in\u0103u|Chi\u015fin\u0103u]], in 1991 he was enrolled at the School of Informatics \u201cTiberiu Popoviciu\u201d in [[Cluj-Napoca]], [[Romania]]. In 1994 he obtained a [[Romanian Baccalaureate|Baccalaureate diploma]]. In the autumn, Candu was admitted to the Faculty of Law of the University \"Babe\u0219-Bolyai\" from Cluj-Napoca, Romania. After four years of study, he was awarded a Bachelor diploma. During September 2007 and June 2008, he studied at the [[Vienna University of Economics and Business Administration]], Institute for Austrian and International Tax Law ([[Vienna]], [[Austria]]), postgraduate International Tax Law Program, where he was awarded a Master's Diploma. In 2001, Andrian Candu participated in the \"Human Rights and Programme Implementation\" course organized by the Institute of European Law in [[Birmingham]], UK. In the same year, Candu obtained certificate of participation in the seminar \"Public administration and individual through the European Convention of Human Rights\" held in the UniDem Campus, [[Venice Commission]] in [[Trieste]], Italy. A year later, at the [[University of the Western Cape|University of Western Cape]], he was attending the International Academy of Human Rights course, on [[Robben Island]], [[Cape Town]], South Africa.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://parlament.md/StructuraParlamentului/Deputies/tabid/87/Id/304/language/en-US/Default.aspx|title=Members of the Parliament of the Republic of Moldova|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Professional activities ==\nIn 1998 he returns to [[Moldova]], where for four years he was principal consultant within the parliamentary Commission for Foreign Policy of the [[Moldova|Republic of Moldova]]. During that period, he began to teach [[international law]] at the Public Administration Academy under the President of the Republic of Moldova. He worked as a lecturer until 2004. \n\nIn 2002 he became senior manager of [[PricewaterhouseCoopers]] Moldova, where he worked until 2010. He was responsible for managing a wide range of projects in the areas of taxation of individuals and businesses, expatriate tax consultancy, [[legal advice]] and other. For a short time in 2010 he served as general manager of Prime Management company, where he was the leader of a team responsible for the management of businesses in different fields and industries including: financial \u2013 banking, real estate, media, hospitality and services. He was a member of the Moldovan International Law Association and CEO of the Moldovan Business People Association.<ref name=\":1\" /> At the end of the same year he was elected member of the [[Parliament of the Republic of Moldova|Parliament of Republic of Moldova]] and member of the Parliamentary Committee Legal, Appointments and Immunities. \n\nIn 2012, the National Political Council of the [[Democratic Party of Moldova]] elected Andrian Candu as vice-president of the party.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pdm.md/en/team/standing-bureau//|title=Standing Bureau of Democratic Party of Moldova|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170325201809/http://www.pdm.md/en/team/standing-bureau//|archive-date=25 March 2017|url-status = dead|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2013 he became Vice-President of the Parliament of Republic of Moldova, a position he held until July 2014 when he was appointed by order of the [[President of Moldova]] Deputy Prime Minister, {{Interlanguage link|lt=Minister of Economy|Minister of Economy (Moldova)|ro|Ministerul Economiei (Republica Moldova)|vertical-align=sup}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministerul_Economiei_(Republica_Moldova)|title=Ministry of Economy of Republic of Moldova|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}{{Circular reference|date=April 2018}}</ref> Half a year later, on January 23, 2015 he was elected [[President of the Moldovan Parliament]] with the votes of 59 lawmakers.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" />\n\nAccording to the last opinion polls carried out in 2019 related to the most popular politicians of the Republic of Moldova, Andrian Candu is placed by some polls on the 10th position among the politicians which are highly trusted by the Moldovans <ref name=\"UNIMEDIA_2019-02-18\">{{Citation | url=https://unimedia.info/ro/news/d8648c3c2edd695a/sondaj-bop-cei-mai-apreciati-politicieni-din-republica-moldova.html| title=Sondaj BOP: Cei mai aprecia\u021bi politicieni din Republica Moldova| newspaper=UNIMEDIA| date= | accessdate=February 18, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"stiri.md_2019-02-18\">{{Citation | url=https://stiri.md/article/politica/sondaj-cine-sunt-politicienii-in-care-moldovenii-au-cea-mai-mare-incredere| title=Sondaj: Cine sunt politicienii \u00een care moldovenii au cea mai mare \u00eencredere| newspaper=stiri.md| date= | accessdate=February 18, 2019}}</ref>  and by some polls on the 13th position.<ref name=\"protv.md_2019-02-18\">{{Citation | url=http://protv.md/stiri/actualitate/partidele-care-ar-ajunge-in-legislativ-daca-duminica-viitoare---2466841.html| title=Partidele care ar ajunge in legislativ daca duminica viitoare ar avea loc alegeri parlamentare. Top trei politicieni care se bucura de cea mai mare incredere. Sondaj iData| newspaper=protv.md| date= | accessdate=February 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn February 19, 2020 Andrian Candu, together with a group of MPs, left the faction of the Democrats and the [[Democratic Party of Moldova|Democratic party]].<ref name=\"Tv8.md/2020/02/19/candu-a-vorbit-cu-plahotniuc-inainte-de-a-pleca-din-pdm-ce-sfat-a-primit-de-la-fostul-lider-al-partidului/_2020-03-12\">{{Citation | url=http://tv8.md/2020/02/19/candu-a-vorbit-cu-plahotniuc-inainte-de-a-pleca-din-pdm-ce-sfat-a-primit-de-la-fostul-lider-al-partidului/| title=Candu a vorbit cu Plahotniuc \u00eenainte de a pleca din PDM. Ce sfat a primit de la fostul lider al partidului| newspaper=Tv8.md/2020/02/19/candu-a-vorbit-cu-plahotniuc-inainte-de-a-pleca-din-pdm-ce-sfat-a-primit-de-la-fostul-lider-al-partidului/| date= | accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Sputnik Moldavian_2020-03-12\">{{Citation | url=https://sputnik.md/politics/20200219/29251125/Candu-Sirbu-Cebotari-democrati-parasit-PDM.html| title=Candu, S\u00eerbu, Cebotari \u0219i al\u021bi democra\u021bi au p\u0103r\u0103sit PDM| newspaper=Sputnik Moldavian| date= | accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref> On February 20, 2020 they announced at the press conference about the establishment of the Pro Moldova parliamentary group.<ref name=\"Diez.md/2020/02/20/sase-ex-democrati-au-constituit-grupul-parlamentar-pro-moldova/_2020-03-12\">{{Citation | url=https://diez.md/2020/02/20/sase-ex-democrati-au-constituit-grupul-parlamentar-pro-moldova/| title=\u0218ase ex-democra\u021bi au constituit grupul parlamentar \"Pro Moldova\" - #diez| newspaper=Diez.md/2020/02/20/sase-ex-democrati-au-constituit-grupul-parlamentar-pro-moldova/| date= | accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"YouTube_2020-03-12\">{{Citation | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lb0lRDks3Uo| title=Constituirea Grupului parlamentar PRO MOLDOVA| newspaper=YouTube| date= | accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Publications ==\nDuring the period of his professional activities, Andrian Candu has prepared materials for publication and publications including: \n* ''\"The contract of sale \u2013 the difference between English and the Romanian law\"'', \n* ''\"European Parliament, organization and activity\"'', \n* ''\"International Commercial Arbitration: the difference between Moldavian, Romanian and Russian\"'', \n* ''\"Commonwealth of Independent States, success or failure?\"'', \n* ''\"Abuses of double taxation treaties\"'', \n* ''\"Evolution of tax treaties \u2013 country report, Romania\"''.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":2\" />\n\n== Personal life ==\nAndrian Candu is married with Zuzana Stasna and has three children, Daniel, Vera and Adam.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.prime.md/ro/andrian-candu-a-devenit-tata-pentru-a-treia-oara_50994.html|title=Andrian Candu, father for the third time\", prime.md|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Andrian Candu speaks fluent in English and Russian.\n\n== Honours ==\nIn April 2015, by a decree of the former [[President of Moldova]] [[Nicolae Timofti]], Andrian Candu was awarded the [[Order of Honour (Moldova)|Order of Honor]]. The politician has received this state award for appreciation of the contribution to reforms based on European values and standards, for outstanding achievements in ensuring the negotiation, signing and ratification of the [[Moldova\u2013European Union Association Agreement|Association Agreement Moldova \u2013 European Union]], for contribution to visa liberalization with EU [[Member state of the European Union|Member States]] and [[Schengen Area|Schengen]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://presedinte.md/rom/presa/presedintele-nicolae-timofti-a-acordat-distinctii-de-stat-unui-grup-de-cetateni-41834|title=President Nicolae Timofti granted state awards to a group of citizens\", presedinte.md|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018 he was awarded by [[Liviu Dragnea]] with the Parliament, necklace which is the highest award of the [[Chamber of Deputies (Romania)|Chamber of Deputies of the Romanian Parliament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ro.sputnik.md/moldova/20181127/23262753/Dragnea-si-Tariceanu-decorati-cu-Medalia-Democratiei-FOTO.html |title=Dragnea \u0219i T\u0103riceanu, decora\u021bi cu Medalia Democra\u021biei |work=Sputnik |date=November 27, 2018 |accessdate=November 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.candu.md/ Adrian Candu Blog]\n* [http://www.parlament.md/StructuraParlamentului/Deputies/tabid/87/Id/304/Default.aspx Adrian Candu's Biography on the site of the Parliament of Moldova]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Candu, Andrian}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Moldovan Parliament]]\n[[Category:Democratic Party of Moldova MPs]]\n[[Category:Democratic Party of Moldova politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Chi\u0219in\u0103u]]\n[[Category:Moldovan MPs 2010\u20132014]]\n[[Category:Moldovan MPs 2014\u20132018]]\n[[Category:Babe\u0219-Bolyai University alumni]]\n[[Category:Vienna University of Economics and Business alumni]]\n[[Category:Moldovan Ministers of Economy]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of Honour (Moldova)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name = Andrian Candu\n| image = A Candu 2.jpg\n| image_size = \n| office = Member of the [[Moldovan Parliament]]\n| office2 = 11th [[President of the Moldovan Parliament]]\n| president2 = [[Nicolae Timofti]]<br/>[[Igor Dodon]]\n| office1 = \n| predecessor2 = [[Igor Corman]]\n| successor2 = [[Zinaida Grecean\u00eei]]\n| office3 = [[Cabinet of Moldova|Deputy Prime Minister]]\n| birth_name = Andrian Candu\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1975|11|27|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Chi\u0219in\u0103u]], [[Moldovan SSR]], USSR\n| spouse = {{Marriage|Zuzana Stastna|2009}}\n| children = Daniel<br>Vera<br>Adam\n| party = Pro Moldova\n| alma_mater = [[Babe\u0219-Bolyai University]]\n| awards = [[File:Ordinul de Onoare.jpg|35px|link=Order of Honour (Moldova)]]\n| website = {{URL|www.candu.md}}\n| primeminister2 = [[Iurie Leanc\u0103]]<br/>[[Chiril Gaburici]]<br/>[[Valeriu Strele\u021b]]<br/>[[Pavel Filip]]\n| primeminister3 = [[Iurie Leanc\u0103]]\n| president3 = [[Nicolae Timofti]]\n| successor3 = [[Stephane Christophe Bride]]\n| termend2 = 24 February 2019\n| termend5 = 11 July 2014\n| termstart5 = 30 May 2013\n| predcessor5 = [[Vladimir Plahotniuc]]\n| successor5 = [[Sergiu S\u00eerbu]]\n| primeminister5 = [[Iurie Leanc\u0103]]\n| president5 = [[Nicolae Timofti]]\n| office5 = [[Moldovan Parliament|Deputy Speaker of the Moldovan Parliament]]\n| termend4 = 23 January 2015\n| termstart4 = 11 July 2014\n| predecessor4 = [[Valeriu Laz\u0103r]]\n| office4 = [[Ministry of Economy and Infrastructure (Moldova)|Minister of Economy]]\n| termstart2 = 23 January 2015\n| predecessor3 = [[Valeriu Laz\u0103r]]\n| successor4 = [[Stephane Christophe Bride]]\n| president4 = [[Nicolae Timofti]]\n| primeminister4 = [[Iurie Leanc\u0103]]\n| termstart = 30 November 2014\n| termend3 = 23 January 2015\n| termstart3 = 11 July 2014\n| termstart1 = 28 November 2010\n| termend1 = 11 July 2014\n| predecessor5 = [[Vladimir Plahotniuc]]\n}}\n'''Andrian Candu''' (born 27 November 1975, in [[Chi\u0219in\u0103u]]) is a [[Moldova]]n politician and a member of the Moldovan Parliament since December 2014. Since 23 January 2015 he has served as the [[President of the Moldovan Parliament|President]] of the [[Parliament of the Republic of Moldova]],<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pre\u0219edintele_Parlamentului_Republicii_Moldova|title=Presidents of the Parliament of the Republic of Moldova|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}{{Circular reference|date=April 2018}}</ref> though his claim to the office has been disputed by [[Zinaida Grecean\u00eei]] since 8 June 2019, as was part of the [[2019 Moldovan constitutional crisis|constitutional crisis]]. Before that, Candu was a [[Deputy Prime Minister]], [[Minister of Economy]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministerul_Economiei_(Republica_Moldova)|title=Ministry of Economy of the Republic of Moldova|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}{{Circular reference|date=April 2018}}</ref> of the [[Republic of Moldova]] since 3 July 2014, and served as [[Deputy Speaker]] of the Parliament of the [[Republic of Moldova]]. He was member of the Parliament of Republic of Moldova between December 2010, and July 2014.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=http://candu.md/despre-mine/|title=CV Andrian Candu|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170325024711/http://candu.md/despre-mine/|archive-date=25 March 2017|url-status = dead|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Biography ==\nAndrian Candu was born in November 27, 1975. After Andrian Candu finished his secondary education at school No. 25, currently Lyceum \"Onisifor Ghibu\", [[Chi\u0219in\u0103u|Chi\u015fin\u0103u]], in 1991 he was enrolled at the School of Informatics \u201cTiberiu Popoviciu\u201d in [[Cluj-Napoca]], [[Romania]]. In 1994 he obtained a [[Romanian Baccalaureate|Baccalaureate diploma]]. In the autumn, Candu was admitted to the Faculty of Law of the University \"Babe\u0219-Bolyai\" from Cluj-Napoca, Romania. After four years of study, he was awarded a Bachelor diploma. During September 2007 and June 2008, he studied at the [[Vienna University of Economics and Business Administration]], Institute for Austrian and International Tax Law ([[Vienna]], [[Austria]]), postgraduate International Tax Law Program, where he was awarded a Master's Diploma. In 2001, Andrian Candu participated in the \"Human Rights and Programme Implementation\" course organized by the Institute of European Law in [[Birmingham]], UK. In the same year, Candu obtained certificate of participation in the seminar \"Public administration and individual through the European Convention of Human Rights\" held in the UniDem Campus, [[Venice Commission]] in [[Trieste]], Italy. A year later, at the [[University of the Western Cape|University of Western Cape]], he was attending the International Academy of Human Rights course, on [[Robben Island]], [[Cape Town]], South Africa.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web|url=http://parlament.md/StructuraParlamentului/Deputies/tabid/87/Id/304/language/en-US/Default.aspx|title=Members of the Parliament of the Republic of Moldova|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== Professional activities ==\nIn 1998 he returns to [[Moldova]], where for four years he was principal consultant within the parliamentary Commission for Foreign Policy of the [[Moldova|Republic of Moldova]]. During that period, he began to teach [[international law]] at the Public Administration Academy under the President of the Republic of Moldova. He worked as a lecturer until 2004. \n\nIn 2002 he became senior manager of [[PricewaterhouseCoopers]] Moldova, where he worked until 2010. He was responsible for managing a wide range of projects in the areas of taxation of individuals and businesses, expatriate tax consultancy, [[legal advice]] and other. For a short time in 2010 he served as general manager of Prime Management company, where he was the leader of a team responsible for the management of businesses in different fields and industries including: financial \u2013 banking, real estate, media, hospitality and services. He was a member of the Moldovan International Law Association and CEO of the Moldovan Business People Association.<ref name=\":1\" /> At the end of the same year he was elected member of the [[Parliament of the Republic of Moldova|Parliament of Republic of Moldova]] and member of the Parliamentary Committee Legal, Appointments and Immunities. \n\nIn 2012, the National Political Council of the [[Democratic Party of Moldova]] elected Andrian Candu as vice-president of the party.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.pdm.md/en/team/standing-bureau//|title=Standing Bureau of Democratic Party of Moldova|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170325201809/http://www.pdm.md/en/team/standing-bureau//|archive-date=25 March 2017|url-status = dead|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2013 he became Vice-President of the Parliament of Republic of Moldova, a position he held until July 2014 when he was appointed by order of the [[President of Moldova]] Deputy Prime Minister, {{Interlanguage link|lt=Minister of Economy|Minister of Economy (Moldova)|ro|Ministerul Economiei (Republica Moldova)|vertical-align=sup}}.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ro.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ministerul_Economiei_(Republica_Moldova)|title=Ministry of Economy of Republic of Moldova|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}{{Circular reference|date=April 2018}}</ref> Half a year later, on January 23, 2015 he was elected [[President of the Moldovan Parliament]] with the votes of 59 lawmakers.<ref name=\":0\" /><ref name=\":1\" />\n\nAccording to the last opinion polls carried out in 2019 related to the most popular politicians of the Republic of Moldova, Andrian Candu is placed by some polls on the 10th position among the politicians which are highly trusted by the Moldovans <ref name=\"UNIMEDIA_2019-02-18\">{{Citation | url=https://unimedia.info/ro/news/d8648c3c2edd695a/sondaj-bop-cei-mai-apreciati-politicieni-din-republica-moldova.html| title=Sondaj BOP: Cei mai aprecia\u021bi politicieni din Republica Moldova| newspaper=UNIMEDIA| date= | accessdate=February 18, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"stiri.md_2019-02-18\">{{Citation | url=https://stiri.md/article/politica/sondaj-cine-sunt-politicienii-in-care-moldovenii-au-cea-mai-mare-incredere| title=Sondaj: Cine sunt politicienii \u00een care moldovenii au cea mai mare \u00eencredere| newspaper=stiri.md| date= | accessdate=February 18, 2019}}</ref>  and by some polls on the 13th position.<ref name=\"protv.md_2019-02-18\">{{Citation | url=http://protv.md/stiri/actualitate/partidele-care-ar-ajunge-in-legislativ-daca-duminica-viitoare---2466841.html| title=Partidele care ar ajunge in legislativ daca duminica viitoare ar avea loc alegeri parlamentare. Top trei politicieni care se bucura de cea mai mare incredere. Sondaj iData| newspaper=protv.md| date= | accessdate=February 18, 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn February 19, 2020 Andrian Candu, together with a group of MPs, left the faction of the Democrats and the [[Democratic Party of Moldova|Democratic party]].<ref name=\"Tv8.md/2020/02/19/candu-a-vorbit-cu-plahotniuc-inainte-de-a-pleca-din-pdm-ce-sfat-a-primit-de-la-fostul-lider-al-partidului/_2020-03-12\">{{Citation | url=http://tv8.md/2020/02/19/candu-a-vorbit-cu-plahotniuc-inainte-de-a-pleca-din-pdm-ce-sfat-a-primit-de-la-fostul-lider-al-partidului/| title=Candu a vorbit cu Plahotniuc \u00eenainte de a pleca din PDM. Ce sfat a primit de la fostul lider al partidului| newspaper=Tv8.md/2020/02/19/candu-a-vorbit-cu-plahotniuc-inainte-de-a-pleca-din-pdm-ce-sfat-a-primit-de-la-fostul-lider-al-partidului/| date= | accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"Sputnik Moldavian_2020-03-12\">{{Citation | url=https://sputnik.md/politics/20200219/29251125/Candu-Sirbu-Cebotari-democrati-parasit-PDM.html| title=Candu, S\u00eerbu, Cebotari \u0219i al\u021bi democra\u021bi au p\u0103r\u0103sit PDM| newspaper=Sputnik Moldavian| date= | accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref> On February 20, 2020 they announced at the press conference about the establishment of the Pro Moldova parliamentary group.<ref name=\"Diez.md/2020/02/20/sase-ex-democrati-au-constituit-grupul-parlamentar-pro-moldova/_2020-03-12\">{{Citation | url=https://diez.md/2020/02/20/sase-ex-democrati-au-constituit-grupul-parlamentar-pro-moldova/| title=\u0218ase ex-democra\u021bi au constituit grupul parlamentar \"Pro Moldova\" - #diez| newspaper=Diez.md/2020/02/20/sase-ex-democrati-au-constituit-grupul-parlamentar-pro-moldova/| date= | accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"YouTube_2020-03-12\">{{Citation | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=lb0lRDks3Uo| title=Constituirea Grupului parlamentar PRO MOLDOVA| newspaper=YouTube| date= | accessdate=March 12, 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Publications ==\nDuring the period of his professional activities, Andrian Candu has prepared materials for publication and publications including: \n* ''\"The contract of sale \u2013 the difference between English and the Romanian law\"'', \n* ''\"European Parliament, organization and activity\"'', \n* ''\"International Commercial Arbitration: the difference between Moldavian, Romanian and Russian\"'', \n* ''\"Commonwealth of Independent States, success or failure?\"'', \n* ''\"Abuses of double taxation treaties\"'', \n* ''\"Evolution of tax treaties \u2013 country report, Romania\"''.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref name=\":2\" />\n\n== Personal life ==\nAndrian Candu is married with Zuzana Stasna and has three children, Daniel, Vera and Adam.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.prime.md/ro/andrian-candu-a-devenit-tata-pentru-a-treia-oara_50994.html|title=Andrian Candu, father for the third time\", prime.md|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> Andrian Candu speaks fluent in English and Russian.\n\n== Honours ==\nIn April 2015, by a decree of the former [[President of Moldova]] [[Nicolae Timofti]], Andrian Candu was awarded the [[Order of Honour (Moldova)|Order of Honor]]. The politician has received this state award for appreciation of the contribution to reforms based on European values and standards, for outstanding achievements in ensuring the negotiation, signing and ratification of the [[Moldova\u2013European Union Association Agreement|Association Agreement Moldova \u2013 European Union]], for contribution to visa liberalization with EU [[Member state of the European Union|Member States]] and [[Schengen Area|Schengen]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://presedinte.md/rom/presa/presedintele-nicolae-timofti-a-acordat-distinctii-de-stat-unui-grup-de-cetateni-41834|title=President Nicolae Timofti granted state awards to a group of citizens\", presedinte.md|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018 he was awarded by [[Liviu Dragnea]] with the Parliament, necklace which is the highest award of the [[Chamber of Deputies (Romania)|Chamber of Deputies of the Romanian Parliament]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ro.sputnik.md/moldova/20181127/23262753/Dragnea-si-Tariceanu-decorati-cu-Medalia-Democratiei-FOTO.html |title=Dragnea \u0219i T\u0103riceanu, decora\u021bi cu Medalia Democra\u021biei |work=Sputnik |date=November 27, 2018 |accessdate=November 27, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.candu.md/ Adrian Candu Blog]\n* [http://www.parlament.md/StructuraParlamentului/Deputies/tabid/87/Id/304/Default.aspx Adrian Candu's Biography on the site of the Parliament of Moldova]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Candu, Andrian}}\n[[Category:1975 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the Moldovan Parliament]]\n[[Category:Democratic Party of Moldova MPs]]\n[[Category:Democratic Party of Moldova politicians]]\n[[Category:People from Chi\u0219in\u0103u]]\n[[Category:Moldovan MPs 2010\u20132014]]\n[[Category:Moldovan MPs 2014\u20132018]]\n[[Category:Babe\u0219-Bolyai University alumni]]\n[[Category:Vienna University of Economics and Business alumni]]\n[[Category:Moldovan Ministers of Economy]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Order of Honour (Moldova)]]\n", "name_user": "Stefan Rotaru", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrian_Candu"}
