te=17 April 2019}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Gully Boy'''''<!--Do not add a translation as the title is in Indian English--> is a 2019 Indian [[Hindi|Hindi-language]] [[Musical film#Indian musical films|musical drama]] film directed by [[Zoya Akhtar]], and written by Zoya Akhtar and [[Reema Kagti]]. The film is produced by [[Ritesh Sidhwani]], Zoya Akhtar and [[Farhan Akhtar]] under the banners of [[Tiger Baby Films]] and [[Excel Entertainment]] productions, with [[Nas]] as an executive producer. It stars [[Ranveer Singh]] and [[Alia Bhatt]], and features [[Kalki Koechlin]], [[Siddhant Chaturvedi]] and [[Vijay Raaz]] in supporting roles. Inspired by the lives of [[Indian hip hop|Indian street rappers]] [[Divine (rapper)|Divine]] and [[Naezy]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2019/jan/10/meet-the-real-life-gully-boys-divine-and-naezy-1923293.html|title=Meet the real-life Gully Boys, Divine and Naezy|newspaper=[[The New Indian Express]]|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref> the film is a [[coming-of-age story]] about an aspiring street rapper from the [[Dharavi]] slums of [[Mumbai]].\n\n[[Principal photography]] for ''Gully Boy'' began in January 2018 and wrapped up in April 2018. It was premiered at the [[Berlin International Film Festival]] on 9 February 2019 and released on 15 February 2019 to positive reviews from critics. With a global gross of over {{INR|238 [[crore]]}} ({{US$|{{To USD|2380|IND|round=yes}} million|long=no}}), it emerged as the [[List of Bollywood films of 2019|seventh-highest-grossing Hindi film of the year]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/box-office-collections/worldwide/2019/|title=Bollywood Top Grossers Worldwide|newspaper=[[Bollywood Hungama]]|accessdate=27 June 2019}}</ref> It was selected as the [[List of Indian submissions for the Academy Award for Best International Feature Film|Indian entry]] for the [[Academy Award for Best International Feature Film|Best International Feature Film]] at the [[92nd Academy Awards]], but it was not nominated.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/bollywood/gully-boy-is-indias-entry-for-oscars-2020-6016405/|title=Ranveer Singh starrer Gully Boy is India's entry for Oscars 2020|date=21 September 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/gully-boy-ranveer-singh-and-alia-bhatt-starrer-is-out-of-the-oscars-2020-race-read-more/articleshow/72809969.cms|title='Gully Boy': Ranveer Singh and Alia Bhatt starrer is out of the Oscars 2020 race, read more - Times of India|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=17 December 2019}}</ref> ''Gully Boy'' won a record 13 [[Filmfare Awards]], including [[Filmfare Award for Best Film|Best Film]], [[Filmfare Award for Best Director|Best Director]], [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] (Singh) and [[Filmfare Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]] (Bhatt), and became the second film to win all four acting awards, 21 years after [[Kuch Kuch Hota Hai]] (1998).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/filmfare-awards-2020-full-list-of-winners-gully-boy-s-13-wins-make-history-alia-bhatt-and-ranveer-singh-take-top-awards/story-JRWvCT8f2A8KxDy94AZYSI.html|title=Filmfare Awards 2020 full list of winners: Gully Boy's 13 wins make history, Alia Bhatt and Ranveer Singh take top awards|work=Hindustan Times|date=16 February 2020|accessdate=17 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nMurad Ahmed ([[Ranveer Singh]]), a final year college student, lives in the [[Dharavi]] [[slums]] of [[Mumbai]]. His abusive father Aftab Shakir Ahmed ([[Vijay Raaz]]) brings home a much younger second wife, much to the chagrin of the family. Murad nurtures a fascination for [[rap]] music. His longtime and overtly possessive girlfriend Safeena Firdausi ([[Alia Bhatt]]) is training to be a surgeon and routinely meets him in secret. \n\nForced to work part-time as a chauffeur after his father is injured, Murad starts to write, with his lyrics informed by the inequalities he observes while on the job. Making the acquaintance of local rapper Shrikant \"MC Sher\" Bhosle ([[Siddhant Chaturvedi]]) whom he saw performing in his college fest, he is drawn into performing his lyrics at underground shows and rap battles and eventually uploading a video on YouTube.\n\n[[Berklee College of Music|Berklee College]] student Shweta \"Sky\" Mehta ([[Kalki Koechlin]]), an evolving musician, reaches out to Murad and Sher after seeing the video, offering to collaborate on a new song. The accompanying video, which is shot in Dharavi, rapidly becomes popular. Murad shares an intimate moment with Sky, later lying to Safeena about it. When Safeena finds out, she reacts violently towards Sky by smashing a bottle of beer on her head. \n\nAs a result, she is brought in by the police but is not arrested as Sky doesn't press charges against her. Murad eventually breaks up with Safeena due to her possessive attitude. As Aftab's violence towards him, his brother and his mother escalates, Murad decides to leave home with his mother and brother and work full-time for his uncle Ateeq Khan ([[Vijay Maurya]]).\n\nLater, when Sky expresses her romantic feelings for him, he declines her as he still loves Safeena and decides to reconcile with her. Murad and Sher enter a contest to open for [[Nas]] at his Mumbai concert, and Murad advances to the finals after a successful rap battle. Murad's confidence grows from interacting with rap fans' appreciation of his performances, and he finally stands up to Aftab and Ateeq when they belittle his passion. He later gets back together with Safeena. He goes on to win the contest and becomes one of India's top rappers. The film ends with his friends, family  and Safeena watching him happily as he begins his opening performance.\n\n==Cast==\n{{colbegin}}\n*[[Ranveer Singh]] as Murad Ahmed a.k.a. Gully Boy\n*[[Alia Bhatt]] as Safeena Firdausi\n*[[Siddhant Chaturvedi]] as Shrikant Bhosle a.k.a. MC Sher\n*[[Vijay Raaz]] as Aftab Ahmed\n*[[Vijay Varma]] as Moeen Arif\n*[[Amruta Subhash]] as Razia Ahmed\n*Ikhlaque Khan as Nasir Firdausi, Safeena's father\n*[[Sheeba Chaddha]] as Hamida Firdausi, Safeena's mother\n*[[Kalki Koechlin]] as Shweta a.k.a. Sky\n*Ayaan Zubair Rahmani as Safeena's brother\n*Rahul Piske as Chintoo\n*[[Jyoti Subhash]] as Dadi\n*Nakul Roshan Sahdev as Salman\n*Shruti Chauhan as Maya\n*[[Vijay Maurya]] as Ateeq Khan, Murad's uncle\n*Srishti Shrivastava as Albina Dadarkar\n*Malika Singh as Suhani\n*Tina Bhatia as Parveen\n*Rahil Gilani as Rishi\n*Rahul Shahani as Shah Rule\n*Svar Kamble as Suhail\n*Chaitnya Sharma as MC Checkmate\n*[[Jasleen Royal]] as Juhi\n*Michaela Tanwar as Gemma\n*[[Kubra Sait]] as Scarlett\n*[[Manj Musik]] as himself\n*Bilal Shaikh as himself\n*Omi Kashyap as Driver\n*[[Raja Kumari]] as herself\n*Emiway as Emiway Bantai\n*Divine as himself as a DJ in a bar\n{{colend}}\n\n==Production==\nAkhtar has co-opted the story of two Mumbai based MCs, [[Naezy]] and [[Divine (rapper)|Divine]], into a musical story portraying a struggle of an aspiring rapper and his surroundings that influence his journey.<ref>{{Citation|last=Film Companion|title=Zoya Akhtar Interview with Anupama Chopra {{!}} Gully Boy {{!}} Film Companion|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Zs_58AocYi4|access-date=7 February 2019}}</ref> Principal photography of the film began in January 2018<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-alia-bhatt-ranveer-singh-s-gully-boy-goes-on-floors-today-2575311|title=Alia Bhatt, Ranveer Singh's 'Gully Boy' goes on floors today|date=14 January 2018|work=[[Daily News and Analysis]]|access-date=14 January 2018}}</ref> and it was wrapped up by April 2018.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BfAnff1ngYL/|title=Alia on Instagram: \"Gully Boy. 14th February 2019\"|website=Instagram.com|access-date=10 February 2018}}</ref> American rapper [[Nas]] is an executive producer for the film.<ref name=\"hotnewhiphop\">{{cite news |title=Nas Joins Divine, Naezy & Ranveer Singh For \"NY Se Mumbai\" |url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/nas-joins-divine-naezy-and-ranveer-singh-for-ny-se-mumbai-new-song.1982047.html |accessdate=1 March 2019 |work=HotNewHipHop |date=19 February 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"rollingstone\">{{cite news |title=Hear Nas Jump In with Divine and Naezy on 'NY Se Mumbai' - |url=https://rollingstoneindia.com/hear-nas-jump-divine-naezy-ny-se-mumbai/ |accessdate=1 March 2019 |work=[[Rolling Stone]] |date=12 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Gully Boy\n| type         = soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Divine (rapper)|Divine]], [[Naezy]], Dub Sharma, Ankur Tewari, Spitfire, Sez on the beat, [[Rishi Rich]], [[Raghu Dixit]], [[Midival Punditz]], [[Karsh Kale]], Chandrashekhar Kunder, [[Jasleen Royal]], [[Mickey McCleary]], Ace, [[Ishq Bector]], Prem-Hardeep, Viveick Rajagopalan and Kaam Bhaari\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 12 January 2019\n| recorded     = \n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = {{Duration|m=46|s=38}}\n| label        = [[Zee Music Company]]\n| language     = [[Hindi]]\n| producer     = \n| compiler     = Ankur Tewari\n| prev_title   = \n| prev_year    = \n| next_title   = \n| next_year    = \n| misc         = {{External media\n | audio1 = {{YouTube|Wp31HBq3BG4|Audio Jukebox}}\n }} {{Singles\n | name = Gully Boy\n | type = soundtrack\n | single1 = Asli Hip Hop\n | single1date = 4 January 2019\n | single2 = Apna Time Aayega\n | single2date = 11 January 2019\n | single3 = Mere Gully Mein\n | single3date = 18 January 2019\n | single4 = Doori\n | single4date = 26 January 2019\n | single5 = Azadi\n | single5date = 8 February 2019\n | single6 = Train Song\n | single6date = 17 February 2019\n | single7 = India 91\n | single7date = 23 February 2019\n | single8 = Jahaan Tu Chala\n | single8date = 23 February 2019\n | single9 = Sher Aaya Sher\n | single9date = 26 February 2019\n }}\n}}\nThe 18-song soundtrack which was released in all streaming platforms on 12 January 2019, involves an estimated 54 contributors, which include rappers from across the country, deejays, music producers and beatboxers, such as [[Divine (rapper)|Divine]], [[Naezy]], Sez on the beat, [[Rishi Rich]], Dub Sharma, [[Jasleen Royal]], Ace, [[Ishq Bector]], MC Altaf, MC TodFod, 100 RBH, Maharya, Noxious D, Viveick Rajagopalan, and others.<ref name=\"scroll.in\">{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/reel/908804/gully-boy-music-four-years-18-songs-54-collaborators-and-an-absolutely-nuts-ranveer-singh|title='Gully Boy' music: Four years, 18 songs, 54 collaborators, and an 'absolutely nuts' Ranveer Singh|first=Devarsi|last=Ghosh|website=Scroll.in|accessdate=10 December 2019}}</ref> As music supervisor, [https://scroll.in/reel/908804/gully-boy-music-four-years-18-songs-54-collaborators-and-an-absolutely-nuts-ranveer-singh Ankur Tewari] has worked with these diverse group of artists in the studio, aiming to \u201cbring the two worlds of hip hop and Bollywood together\u201d.<ref name=\"scroll.in\"/>\n\nA promotional single for the film, \"NY Se Mumbai\", was released on 9 February 2019 and performed by Divine, Naezy and [[Ranveer Singh]] along with American rapper [[Nas]].<ref name=\"hotnewhiphop\"/><ref name=\"rollingstone\"/> The track was produced by XD Pro Music, a [[Toronto]] based producer duo, and Ill Wayno.\n\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| headline = Track listing\n| total_length = 46:38\n| title1 = Asli Hip Hop\n| extra1 = [[Ranveer Singh]]\n| lyrics1 = Spitfire\n| music1 = Spitfire\n| length1 = 1:40\n| title2 = Mere Gully Mein\n| extra2 = {{Hlist|Ranveer Singh|[[Divine (rapper)|Divine]]|Naezy}}\n| lyrics2 = {{Hlist|Divine|Naezy}}\n| music2 = {{Hlist|Divine|Naezy|Sez on the Beat}}\n| length2 = 3:05\n| title3 = Doori Poem\n| extra3 = Ranveer Singh\n| lyrics3 = [[Javed Akhta