ra17 = {{Hlist|[[Kaka Bhaniawala]]|Arjun|Blitz|Desi Ma}}\n| music17 = {{Hlist|Prem|Hardeep}}\n| lyrics17 = {{Hlist|Bhinder Khanpuri|Arjun|Blitz|Desi Ma}}\n| length17 = 3:48\n| title18 = India 91\n| extra18 = {{Hlist|MC Altaf|MC TodFod|100 RBH|Maharya|Noxious D}}\n| music18 = {{Hlist|Viveick Rajagopalan|Akshay Dhawan}}\n| lyrics18 = {{Hlist|MC Altaf|MC TodFod|100 RBH|Maharya|Noxious D|MC Mawali}}\n| length18 = 3:14\n}}\n\n== Marketing and release ==\n[[File:Ranveer Singh and Alia Bhatt in 2019.jpg|thumb|upright=1.1|[[Ranveer Singh]] and [[Alia Bhatt]] at the trailer launch of ''Gully Boy'']]\n[[File:Apna Time Ayyega.jpg|thumb|Graffiti of Apna Time Aayega in Mumbai]]\n''Gully Boy'' was confirmed to be releasing on 14 February 2019 by\nAlia Bhatt.<ref name=\":0\" /> The first look official poster of the film released on 1 January 2019 and reconfirmed the release date to be 14 February 2019.<ref name=\"poster\">{{cite news|url=https://m.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/ranveer-singh-alia-bhatt-share-first-gully-boy-poster-check-it-out-here/story-aWRYtVEmr5dHlZiouSSijN.html|title=Ranveer Singh, Alia Bhatt share first Gully Boy poster|work=Hindustan Times|date=1 January 2019|accessdate=1 January 2019}}</ref> Two new theatrical posters revealing looks of lead actors of the film unveiled for the public on 2 January 2019.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/alia-bhatt-and-ranveer-singhs-looks-from-gully-boy-revealed-check-out-the-new-posters/340239|title=Alia Bhatt and Ranveer Singh's looks from Gully Boy revealed! Check out the new posters|work=Times Now News|date=2 January 2019|accessdate=2 January 2019}}</ref> The trailer announcement was made on 4 January 2019 with a small teaser in which [[Ranveer Singh]] is seen rapping. The official trailer of the film was released on 9 January 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=JfbxcD6biOk|title=Gully Boy - Official Trailer - Ranveer Singh - Alia Bhatt - Zoya Akhtar|via=[[YouTube]]}}</ref>\nThe film has been selected in Berlinale Special section of [[69th Berlin International Film Festival]]. The film was screened on 9 February 2019 for its world premiere at the festival.<ref name=\"Hindustan Times\"/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/magazines/panache/ranveer-singh-alia-bhatt-starrer-gully-boy-to-have-world-premiere-at-69th-berlin-film-fest/articleshow/67088636.cms|title=Ranveer Singh, Alia Bhatt-starrer 'Gully Boy' to have world premiere at 69th Berlin Film Fest|newspaper=[[The Economic Times]]|date=14 December 2018}}</ref>  It was released in India on 14 February 2019<ref name=\":0\"/> on 3,350 screens and in overseas market on 751 screens, with a worldwide count of 4,101 screens.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=taran_adarsh|author=Taran Adarsh|date=14 February 2019|number=1095956688698392577?s=19|title=#GullyBoy screen count... India: 3350 Overseas: 751 Worldwide total: 4101 screens}}</ref>\n\nSome writers speculated about similarities between ''Gully Boy'' and the [[Eminem]]-starer ''[[8 Mile (film)|8 Mile]]'' (2002).<ref>Buzz Desk (7 January 2019), [https://www.india.com/buzz/bollywood-news-ranveer-singhs-gully-boy-similar-to-eminems-8-mile-fans-share-their-views-on-twitter-3514991/ \"Ranveer Singh\u2019s Gully Boy Similar to Eminem\u2019s 8 Mile? Fans Share Their Views on Twitter\"], ''India''. Retrieved 19 April 2019.</ref> Writer [[Aditya Magal]] in ''[[The Quint]]'' calling it, though appreciating the movie as entertaining, after outlining what he considers the many similarities, \"an engineered, Indianized version of ''8 Mile''\",<ref>Aditya Magal (27 February 2019), [https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/bollywood/gully-boy-compared-to-8-mile-ranveer-singh-alia-bhatt-zoya-akhtar-eminem \"Why I Think Ranveer\u2019s \u2018Gully Boy\u2019 Is Just Too Similar to \u20188 Mile\u2019\"], ''The Quint''. Retrieved 19 April 2019.</ref> while journalist Rachna Tyagi of ''[[The Week (Indian magazine)|The Week]]'', more harshly, as she rates it 2.5/5, terms it \"a copycat Indian version.\"<ref>Rachna Tyagi (14 February 2019), [https://www.theweek.in/review/movies/2019/02/14/ranveer-singh-gully-boy-bollywood-version-eminem-8-mile.html \"Ranveer Singh's 'Gully Boy' a Bollywood version of Eminem's '8 Mile'\"], ''The Week''. Retrieved 19 April 2019.</ref> Denying the claims, director Zoya Akhtar responded that \"I get it (the comparison). I totally understand it, because that's the reference point and that's what they've seen so, that's the immediate reference point and people here just love to do that.\"<ref>Gaurang Chauhan (15 February 2019), [https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/exclusive-is-ranveer-singh-and-alia-bhatts-gully-boy-inspired-by-eminems-8-mile-zoya-akhtar-answers-watch-video/365904 \"EXCLUSIVE | Is Ranveer Singh and Alia Bhatt's Gully Boy inspired by Eminem's 8 Mile? Zoya Akhtar answers\"], ''Times Now News''. Retrieved 19 April 2019.</ref>\n\n===Home video=== \nThe film was made available as [[Video on demand|VOD]] on [[Prime Video]] on 16 April 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gadgets.ndtv.com/entertainment/news/gully-boy-amazon-prime-video-india-available-release-date-download-2023716|title=Gully Boy Is Now Available on Amazon Prime Video in India|website=NDTV Gadgets 360}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\n===Critical response===  \n''Gully Boy'' received positive reviews from critics with praise directed to Akhtar\u2019s direction, Maurya\u2019s dialogue and Singh,  Chaturvedi and Bhatt for their performances.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/bollywood/entertainment-news-today-amol-palekar-on-ngma-controversy-gully-boy-premiere|title=QuickE: Amol Palekar on NGMA Controversy; 'Gully Boy' Reviews|website=Thequint.com|accessdate=14 February 2019|date=10 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/news/bollywood-news/article/gully-boy-first-reviews-out-ranveer-singhs-career-best-performance-alia-bhatt-is-terrific-say-critics-and-fans/363035|title=Gully Boy FIRST reviews out! Ranveer Singh's career best performance, Alia Bhatt is terrific say critics and fans - Bollywood News|website=Timesnownews.com|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ibtimes.co.in/gully-boy-movie-review-rating-by-critics-ranveer-singhs-career-best-alia-firecracker-791658|title=Gully Boy movie reviews: Ranveer Singh's career best, Alia a firecracker, say Rajeev Masand & Anupama Chopra|first=Shefali|last=Jha|date=10 February 2019|website=Ibtimes.co.in|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref> On [[Rotten Tomatoes]], the film has a score of 95% based on 21 reviews, with an average rating of 8.3/10.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/gully_boy|title=Gully Boy (2019)|accessdate=14 February 2019|website=Rottentomatoes.com}}</ref>\n\n[[Anna M. M. Vetticad]] of ''[[Firstpost]]'' gave ''Gully Boy'' four stars out of five, writing, \"Ranveer Singh and Alia Bhatt are devastatingly good in Zoya Akhtar's ultimate anthem for the rebel\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/gully-boy-movie-review-ranveer-singh-alia-bhatt-are-devastatingly-good-in-zoya-akhtars-ultimate-anthem-for-the-rebel-6083111.html|title=Gully Boy movie review: Ranveer Singh, Alia Bhatt are devastatingly good in Zoya Akhtar's ultimate anthem for the rebel- Entertainment News, Firstpost|date=14 February 2019|website=Firstpost.com|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref> [[Raja Sen]] of ''[[Hindustan Times]]'' called it \"the first great [[Hindi film]] of 2019\",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/gully-boy-movie-review-ranveer-singh-and-alia-bhatt-raise-the-roof-with-a-great-musical-4-stars/story-yvEHUA5dHSApH9FuOT3kMI.html|title=Gully Boy movie review: Ranveer Singh and Alia Bhatt raise the roof with a great musical. 4 stars|date=14 February 2019|website=Hindustan Times|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref> while [[Taran Adarsh]] of [[Bollywood Hungama]] went on to call it \"Akhtar\u2019s best film to date\".<ref>{{cite tweet|user=taran_adarsh|author=Taran Adarsh|date=14 February 2019|number=1095967703251136513?s=19|title=#OneWordReview\u2026 #GullyBoy: FANTASTIC. Rating: \u2b50\ufe0f\u2b50\ufe0f\u2b50\ufe0f\u2b50\ufe0fDepicts the struggles of an underdog brilliantly... Zoya Akhtar\u2019s best film to date... Ranveer is phenomenal... Alia is electrifying... Siddhant Chaturvedi is super... Not to be missed! #GullyBoyReview https://t.co/f6phWdsb7Q}}</ref> Rachit Gupta of ''[[The Times of India]]'' also gave four stars.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-reviews/gully-boy/movie-review/67981331.cms|title=Gully Boy Review {4/5}: Entertainment ekdum hard hai bhai|accessdate=14 February 2019|website=The Times of India}}</ref> Sukanya Verma of [[Rediff.com]] also gave four stars.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rediff.com/amp/movies/review/gully-boy-review-youll-cry-for-ranveer/20190214.htm|title=Gully Boy Review: You'll cry for Ranveer|publisher=Rediff.com|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref> Livemint wrote, \"It\u2019s a hard-won transformation \u2013 bohot hard \u2013 and it rings true\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.livemint.com/industry/media/film-review-gully-boy-amplifies-a-voice-from-the-streets-1550117990055.html|title=Film review: 'Gully Boy' amplifies a voice from the streets|first=Uday|last=Bhatia|date=14 February 2019|website=Livemint.com|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref> [[Anupama Chopra]] commented, \"By the end, I was wiping tears and cheering furiously not just for Murad, but for each one of these characters to find happiness\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmcompanion.in/gully-boy-movie-review-ranveer-singh-zoya-akhtar-divine-anupama-chopra|title=Gully Boy Is A Superb Love Letter To The Spirit of Mumbai|date=14 February 2019|website=Film Companion}}</ref>\n\n[[Saibal Chatterjee]] of [[NDTV]] opined, \"Gully Boy can be whole-heartedly commended for its craft, fascinating characters and Ranveer Singh. He absolutely kills the slow-burning rapper act. What's more, he does with a lot of energy to spare.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/gully-boy-movie-review-ranveer-singh-kills-it-supported-by-feisty-alia-bhatt-3-out-of-5-stars-1993312|title=Gully Boy Movie Review: Ranveer Singh Kills It, Supported By Feisty Alia Bhatt|website=Ndtv.com|access-date=14 February 2019}}</ref> Writing for Film Companion, [[Baradwaj Rangan]] gave ''Gully Boy'' three stars out of five and found it to be \"softer than expected, but hugely entertaining and beautifully made\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.filmcompanion.in/gully-boy-movie-review-berlin-film-festival-2019-ranveer-singh-zoya-akhtar-baradwaj-rangan|title=Gully Boy Movie Review: A Softer Than Expected, But Hugely Entertaining And Beautifully Made Street-Rapper Story|website=Filmcompanion.in|access-date=10 February 2019|date=9 February 2019}}</ref> Ananya Bhattacharya of ''[[India Today]]'' rated it three stars out of five.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/amp/movies/bollywood/story/gully-boy-movie-review-ranveer-singh-alia-bhatt-1455572-2019-02-13|title=Gully Boy Movie Review: Ranveer Singh raps, Alia Bhatt roars in Zoya Akhtar film|website=Indiatoday.in|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref> Mayur Sanap of [[Deccan Chronicle]] also gave three stars.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/movie-reviews/140219/gully-boy-movie-review-ranveer-singh-alia-bhatt-elevate-zoya-akhtar.html|title=Gully Boy movie review: Ranveer Singh, Alia Bhatt elevate Zoya Akhtar's nuanced drama|first=Mayur|last=Sanap|date=14 February 2019|newspaper=[[Deccan Chronicle]]|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref> ''[[The Wire (India)|The Wire]]'' felt the film dealt with Bollywood tropes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thewire.in/film/gully-boy-movie-review|title=Movie Review: 'Gully Boy' Is Too Self-Contained to Start a Real Conversation|website=Thewire.in|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref>\n\nManjusha Radhakrishnan of [[Gulf News]] rated the film 4/5 and wrote, \"When he breaks down, you break down with him and that\u2019s one of the biggest victories of Gully Boy\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://gulfnews.com/entertainment/bollywood/movie-review-gully-boy-1.1550141854487|title=Movie Review: Gully Boy|website=Gulf News|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref> Among international reviewers, Lee Marshall of ''[[Screen International]]'' wrote, \"Singh busts rhymes with the best of them in this energetic, entertaining film\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.screendaily.com/reviews/gully-boy-berlin-review/5136698.article|title='Gully Boy': Berlin Review|first=Lee|last=Marshall2019-02-09T20:30:00+00:00|website=Screendaily.com|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref> Peter Bradshaw of ''[[The Guardian]]'' gave the film three stars of five.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2019/feb/11/gully-boy-review-berlin-film-festival|title=Gully Boy review \u2013 shy slumdog rapper is a breakout star|first=Peter|last=Bradshaw|date=11 February 2019|accessdate=14 February 2019|website=The Guardian}}</ref> Deborah Young of ''The Hollywood Reporter'' commended Akhtar for her direction.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/gully-boy-review-1184114|title='Gully Boy' ('Apna Time Aayega'): Film Review - Berlin 2019|website=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref> Anita Iyer of ''[[Khaleej Times]]'' rated the film four stars out of five.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.khaleejtimes.com/citytimes/bollywood/gully-boy-review-ranveer-delivers-soul-stirring-performance|title='Gully Boy' review: Ranveer delivers soul-stirring performance|first=Anita|last=Iyer|newspaper=[[Khaleej Times]]|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref> Jay Weissberg of ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' wrote, \"Zoya Akhtar's most accomplished film to date is a mainstream rap musical about a Muslim guy from working-class Mumbai determined to break free from the strictures of expectation and class, all served up with generous helpings of deftly written hip-hop lyrics and a largely well-woven narrative\" starring \"Ranveer Singh in all his charms.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2019/film/reviews/gully-boy-review-1203135142/|title=Berlin Film Review: 'Gully Boy'|first1=Jay|last1=Weissberg|first2=Jay|last2=Weissberg|date=11 February 2019|website=Variety|accessdate=14 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Box office===\n''Gully Boy'' opened with collection of {{INR|19.4 [[crore]]}} on its first day. In two weeks of release, the film grossed {{INR|220 crore}}. The film grossed {{INR|165.58 crore}} in India and {{US$|9.6 million|long=no}} ({{INR|72.58 crore}}) overseas, taking its worldwide gross to {{INR|245.21 crore}} ({{US$|{{To USD|2380|IND}} million|long=no}}).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/gully-boy/box-office//|title=Gully Boy Box Office Collection till Now |work=Bollywood Hungama|accessdate=11 April 2019}}</ref> It is [[List of Bollywood films of 2019|2019's eighth highest-grossing Bollywood film worldwide]].\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{{Main|List of accolades received by Gully Boy}}\n\nThe film won 13 awards at the [[65th Filmfare Awards]], the most awards for a single film in a year, has broken the record of [[Black (2005 film)|Black]], which won 11 awards in [[51st Filmfare Awards|2006]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Bagrecha |first1=Vayushi |title=Gully Boy Bags 13 Awards At Filmfare; Breaks All the Records |url=https://ladpoint.com/gully-boy-bags-13-awards-at-filmfare-breaks-all-the-records/4206/ |accessdate=14 March 2020 |work=LADPOINT |date=16 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Farhan Akhtar ecstatic as Gully Boy breaks record to win most awards for a single film ever at Filmfare 2020 |url=https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/news/farhan-akhtar-ecstatic-gully-boy-breaks-record-win-most-awards-single-film-ever-filmfare-2020-508270 |accessdate=14 March 2020 |work=PINKVILLA |language=en}}</ref> Alongside, the film won 12 awards at [[26th Screen Awards]]<ref>{{cite news |title=Gully Boy dominates Star Screen Awards 2019 - Full list of winners |url=https://www.cinemaexpress.com/stories/news/2019/dec/09/gully-boy-dominates-star-screen-awards-2019--full-list-of-winners-here-15930.html |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=The New Indian Express}}</ref> and 9 awards in [[Zee Cine Awards]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Gully Boy Grabs Maximum Awards Yet Again at Zee Cine Awards 2020 |url=https://www.indiaforums.com/article/gully-boy-grabs-maximum-awards-yet-again-at-zee-cine-awards-2020_161369 |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=India Forums |language=en}}</ref>\nThe film was also [[List of Indian submissions for the Academy Award for Best International Feature Film| India's official entry]] to [[92nd Academy Awards]] for the [[List of submissions to the 92nd Academy Awards for Best International Feature Film|Best International feature film category]] though it was not nominated.<ref>{{cite news |title='Gully Boy' out of Oscar race |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/gully-boy-out-of-oscar-race/article30327283.ece |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=The Hindu |date=17 December 2019 |language=en-IN}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=No Oscars for Gully Boy, Here are 10 Films Shortlisted for Best International Film |url=https://www.news18.com/news/movies/10-films-make-shortlist-for-oscars-best-international-film-gully-boy-fails-to-make-the-cut-2426521.html |accessdate=24 March 2020 |work=News18 |date=17 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of submissions to the 92nd Academy Awards for Best International Feature Film]]\n* [[List of Indian submissions for the Academy Award for Best International Feature Film]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|tt2395469}}\n* [http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/movie/gully-boy/ Gully Boy] on [[Bollywood Hungama]]\n* {{Rotten